In the middle of a free concert in central park, everything suddenly goes to hell as it appears that Cable materializes and shoots Professor Charles Xavier in the head, infecting him with a deadly strain of the Techno-Organic Virus. But all is not as it seems and the X-Men are caught up in the web of vengeance in a desperate battle through time. The event presages Messiah Complex in many ways and despite being received to mixed reviews as it was released, I still find it a compelling read that gives insight into Cable as well as Stryfe and a few others. This torrent contains all 12 issues pf the X-Cutioner's Song saga, all in digital format. The final two files are the first epilogue in Uncanny X-Men 297, as well as Stryfe's Strike File published in 1995. The second epilogue, X-Force 19, is NOT included as I could not find a digital version but after re-reading it I don't think it is necessary to the story. Massive thanks to Meganubis-Empire for the rips, and please seed and enjoy! :-)
